<span key="399aae7441444e5a81616d80abe49e1d"><span offset-key="399aae7441444e5a81616d80abe49e1d:0">Installing</span></span>

<span key="90dc6cdf4279491fbb299ce3f37fed0d"><span offset-key="90dc6cdf4279491fbb299ce3f37fed0d:0">Sequelize is available via </span></span><a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/sequelize" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="816964444e08434aabdfe9d9d5ce6a7a" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-32970_259-32971-237__"><span data-key="076280d614644dd1943f1a62f36ae765"><span data-offset-key="076280d614644dd1943f1a62f36ae765:0">npm</span></span></span></a><span key="2a86c8214dad403897948b4a8f132ab0"><span offset-key="2a86c8214dad403897948b4a8f132ab0:0"> (or </span></span><a href="https://yarnpkg.com/package/sequelize" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="7b3c60f6b97446f4881dea81ae28f585" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-32970_259-32971-237__"><span data-key="a1c816ea9f464b8a8d848725694fbc83"><span data-offset-key="a1c816ea9f464b8a8d848725694fbc83:0">yarn</span></span></span></a><span key="3f2c5aed4b7c411dbb85c7dd96d9f0c1"><span offset-key="3f2c5aed4b7c411dbb85c7dd96d9f0c1:0">).</span></span>

## 

<span key="137c3b457dd546b2972eaf0af040f228"><span offset-key="137c3b457dd546b2972eaf0af040f228:0">Connecting to a database</span></span>

<span key="2cc40db052a845fd820348f3c314ed0e"><span offset-key="2cc40db052a845fd820348f3c314ed0e:0">To connect to the database, you must create a Sequelize instance. 1

<span key="77615935f68c4397b311c32f147169dc"><span offset-key="77615935f68c4397b311c32f147169dc:0">const { Sequelize } = require('sequelize');</span></span>

4

<span key="b77c0216f0474e7bb0c174b378870171"><span offset-key="b77c0216f0474e7bb0c174b378870171:0">const sequelize = new Sequelize('sqlite::memory:') // Example for sqlite</span></span>

<span key="b3a0a9b0503942ef8186a3d9f1535397"><span offset-key="b3a0a9b0503942ef8186a3d9f1535397:0">const sequelize = new Sequelize('postgres://user:<a href="../../../../../../cdn-cgi/l/email-protection.html" class="__cf_email__">[email protected]</a>:5432/dbname') // Example for postgres</span></span>

<span key="0f9ea9fc39be4f08956172837e995f31"><span offset-key="0f9ea9fc39be4f08956172837e995f31:0">const sequelize = new Sequelize('database', 'username', 'password', {</span></span>

### 

<span key="5dfc3fc9138b4868a91be708e46b4cad"><span offset-key="5dfc3fc9138b4868a91be708e46b4cad:0">Closing the connection</span></span>

<span key="560cf4da55004a81bfffc42b8a9336a9"><span offset-key="560cf4da55004a81bfffc42b8a9336a9:0">Sequelize will keep the connection open by default, and use the same connection for all queries. If you need to close the connection, call </span>`sequelize.close()`<span offset-key="560cf4da55004a81bfffc42b8a9336a9:2"> (which is asynchronous and returns a Promise).</span></span>

## 

<span key="affe99f2345e4b03ae697982e5440508"><span offset-key="affe99f2345e4b03ae697982e5440508:0">Terminology convention</span></span>

<span key="2201d93e2d8d43bd92e979b6ee819f2b"><span offset-key="2201d93e2d8d43bd92e979b6ee819f2b:0">Observe that, in the examples above, </span>`Sequelize`<span offset-key="2201d93e2d8d43bd92e979b6ee819f2b:2"> refers to the library itself while </span>`sequelize`<span offset-key="2201d93e2d8d43bd92e979b6ee819f2b:4"> refers to an instance of Sequelize, which represents a connection to one database. This is the recommended convention and it will be followed throughout the documentation.</span></span>

## 

<span key="a489463a1e754d39a0ad03fddb950a18"><span offset-key="a489463a1e754d39a0ad03fddb950a18:0">Tip for reading the docs</span></span>

<span key="84d8e0e86044497abd3fa3cd502dcab5"><span offset-key="84d8e0e86044497abd3fa3cd502dcab5:0">You are encouraged to run code examples locally while reading the Sequelize docs. This will help you learn faster. The easiest way to do this is using the SQLite dialect:</span></span>

1

<span key="25d5dd6551be403ea98a9f50e6921c7b"><span offset-key="25d5dd6551be403ea98a9f50e6921c7b:0">const { Sequelize, Op, Model, DataTypes } = require("sequelize");</span></span>

2

<span key="5cf47b00cd3e43e988c534fc3961dde6"><span offset-key="5cf47b00cd3e43e988c534fc3961dde6:0">const sequelize = new Sequelize("sqlite::memory:");</span></span>

3

<span key="810873ad4d674842a5075fe9c7b47e0f"><span offset-key="810873ad4d674842a5075fe9c7b47e0f:0"><span slate-zero-width="n">​</span></span></span>

4

<span key="c16914283a7a4d2889ae949dc0bf9635"><span offset-key="c16914283a7a4d2889ae949dc0bf9635:0">// Code here! It works!</span></span>

<img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-h7gdob r-10ptun7 r-1vzi8xi" />

Copied!

<span key="61f42820b86e475796397a7a872be1a1"><span offset-key="61f42820b86e475796397a7a872be1a1:0">To experiment with the other dialects, which are harder to setup locally, you can use the </span></span><a href="https://github.com/papb/sequelize-sscce" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="46edf067664c4b30842ada74c1afe75f" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-32970_259-32971-237__"><span data-key="db6bc108c0414440aef528e410b128bd"><span data-offset-key="db6bc108c0414440aef528e410b128bd:0">Sequelize SSCCE</span></span></span></a><span key="708a32eca13b4e2eb931796c1b8ce2af"><span offset-key="708a32eca13b4e2eb931796c1b8ce2af:0"> GitHub repository, which allows you to run code on all supported dialects directly from GitHub, for free, without any setup!</span></span>

## 

<span key="375788654f0a45af9c83d9f14e62f56a"><span offset-key="375788654f0a45af9c83d9f14e62f56a:0">New databases versus existing databases</span></span>

<span key="a9da9d32fba44aa98b68993ae5e73c16"><span offset-key="a9da9d32fba44aa98b68993ae5e73c16:0">If you are starting a project from scratch, and your database does not exist yet, Sequelize can be used since the beginning in order to automate the creation of every table in your database.</span></span>

<span key="7ebb903d9328465cb1eef9c6a94052cc"><span offset-key="7ebb903d9328465cb1eef9c6a94052cc:0">Also, if you want to use Sequelize to connect to a database that is already filled with tables and data, that works as well! Sequelize has got you covered in both cases.</span></span>

## 

<span key="00996189682c4da2b8a41c56cc96ef7b"><span offset-key="00996189682c4da2b8a41c56cc96ef7b:0">Logging</span></span>

<span key="67c7b873dfe84f1ba018b57089e6d80c"><span offset-key="67c7b873dfe84f1ba018b57089e6d80c:0">By default, Sequelize will log to console every SQL query it performs. The </span>`options.logging`<span offset-key="67c7b873dfe84f1ba018b57089e6d80c:2"> option can be used to customize this behavior, by defining the function that gets executed every time Sequelize would log something. The default value is </span>`console.log`<span offset-key="67c7b873dfe84f1ba018b57089e6d80c:4"> and when using that only the first log parameter of log function call is displayed. For example, for query logging the first parameter is the raw query and the second (hidden by default) is the Sequelize object.</span></span>

<span key="1f341f4e516d45e98546de5dc65310ca"><span offset-key="1f341f4e516d45e98546de5dc65310ca:0">Common useful values for </span>`options.logging`<span offset-key="1f341f4e516d45e98546de5dc65310ca:2">:</span></span>

1

<span key="38c09d07cc1c4ba784a61b7dcb93fba8"><span offset-key="38c09d07cc1c4ba784a61b7dcb93fba8:0">const sequelize = new Sequelize('sqlite::memory:', {</span></span>

2

<span key="3edc04d40e544c749faba33f9da196fd"><span offset-key="3edc04d40e544c749faba33f9da196fd:0"> // Choose one of the logging options</span></span>

3

<span key="13f66a5987d84effafb0142dec5dc0d9"><span offset-key="13f66a5987d84effafb0142dec5dc0d9:0"> logging: console.log, // Default, displays the first parameter of the log function call</span></span>

4

<span key="bbcf17b438ae4cbebea668d10b8c7444"><span offset-key="bbcf17b438ae4cbebea668d10b8c7444:0"> logging: (...msg) => console.log(msg), // Displays all log function call parameters</span></span>

5

<span key="27f5a6b0349a4651bf95463fe5da92b1"><span offset-key="27f5a6b0349a4651bf95463fe5da92b1:0"> logging: false, // Disables logging</span></span>

6

<span key="7fb03393d3a64bcb9d90c76a8aa48120"><span offset-key="7fb03393d3a64bcb9d90c76a8aa48120:0"> logging: msg => logger.debug(msg), // Use custom logger (e.g. Winston or Bunyan), displays the first parameter</span></span>

7

<span key="9a893525544446a3acc87d747814e5b0"><span offset-key="9a893525544446a3acc87d747814e5b0:0"> logging: logger.debug.bind(logger) // Alternative way to use custom logger, displays all messages</span></span>

8

<span key="363d60dab1d64d25b2ce2d0e0849564e"><span offset-key="363d60dab1d64d25b2ce2d0e0849564e:0">});</span></span>

## 

<span key="4b00c6d689c84cab8fd2d07aac60bb1a"><span offset-key="4b00c6d689c84cab8fd2d07aac60bb1a:0">Promises and async/await</span></span>

<span key="115b041e0c734c3a8b3992f37d61783a"><span offset-key="115b041e0c734c3a8b3992f37d61783a:0">Most of the methods provided by Sequelize are asynchronous and therefore return Promises. They are all </span></span><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Promise" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="8c365f0e0fb5457c96104148be352f04" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-32970_259-32971-237__"><span data-key="8bd0a8abab5141559c2fdb86b1b2eb1b"><span data-offset-key="8bd0a8abab5141559c2fdb86b1b2eb1b:0">Promises</span></span></span></a><span key="3d432198bc11472b978ce2707c85f4eb"><span offset-key="3d432198bc11472b978ce2707c85f4eb:0"> , so you can use the Promise API (for example, using </span>`then`<span offset-key="3d432198bc11472b978ce2707c85f4eb:2">, </span>`catch`<span offset-key="3d432198bc11472b978ce2707c85f4eb:4">, </span>`finally`<span offset-key="3d432198bc11472b978ce2707c85f4eb:6">) out of the box.</span></span>

<span key="fb9e67dc47eb41948e3c1a777d91fb14"><span offset-key="fb9e67dc47eb41948e3c1a777d91fb14:0">Of course, using </span>`async`<span offset-key="fb9e67dc47eb41948e3c1a777d91fb14:2"> and </span>`await`<span offset-key="fb9e67dc47eb41948e3c1a777d91fb14:4"> works normally as well.Generated by </span></span><a href="https://esdoc.org" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="cfb61c659f664972a6e6ef43d1409efa" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-32970_259-32971-237__"><span data-key="6a5e7cd83ebd4294a81820c68fc68d26"><span data-offset-key="6a5e7cd83ebd4294a81820c68fc68d26:0">ESDo</span></span></span></a><span key="549a88278f0a4d6dbf62d105e6a1a520"><span offset-key="549a88278f0a4d6dbf62d105e6a1a520:0"><span slate-zero-width="z">​</span></span></span>
